adult male (
<taxonomicName authority=", Gondwanan" authorityName="Gondwanan" box="[946,1209,1963,1988]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Eriococcidae, Gondwanan</taxonomicName>
group) (after 
<bibRefCitation author="Hardy" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hardy" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="497 - 528" refId="ref203062" refString="Hardy, N. B., Beardsley, Jr. J. W. &amp; Gullan, P. J. (2011) Uncovering diversity of Australian Eucalyptus - constrained felt scales (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae). Systematic Entomology, 36, 497 - 528. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.2011.00577. x" type="journal article" year="2011">
Hardy 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
). For abbreviations, see p. 8.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="92.[151,1436,152,323]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,152,179]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Comment.</emphasis>
The adult male of 
<taxonomicName box="[540,672,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Lobimargo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsi">
<emphasis box="[540,672,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">L. williamsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[943,1164,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Stibococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerinus">
<emphasis box="[943,1164,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Stibococcus cerinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having (i) many long fleshy setae, those on the antennae being much longer than the width of each segment (fleshy setae, if present on 
<taxonomicName box="[273,382,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Stibococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerinus">
<emphasis box="[273,382,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">S. cerinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, very similar to hair-like setae and sparce, those on the antennae subequal in length to segment width), (ii) no capitate setae on antennae (present on 
<taxonomicName box="[733,841,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Stibococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cerinus">
<emphasis box="[733,841,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">S. cerinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and (iii) no caudal extensions on abdominal segment VIII (present).
</paragraph>
